olive oil
1 pear
2 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 packet ginger paste
½ tsp brown sugar
½ tbs soy sauce
1 tsp vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)
1 packet Peeled Prawns
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Japanese Dressing
1 packet Crushed Peanuts

• Thinly slice pear into wedges.
• Finely chop garlic.
• Grate carrot.
• In a small bowl, combine garlic, ginger paste, the brown sugar, soy sauce and vinegar.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook peeled prawns, tossing, until pink and starting to curl up,
3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic-ginger mixture and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix, carrot, pear, garlic aioli and Japanese dressing in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper.

• Divide pear slaw between bowls.
• Top with garlic ginger prawns.
• Sprinkle over crushed peanuts to serve. Enjoy!